      • applyOverrides

        @CheckReturnValue
public ScannerSupplier applyOverrides(ErrorProneOptions errorProneOptions)
                               throws InvalidCommandLineOptionException
        Applies an override map (from command-line options) to this ScannerSupplier and returns the resulting ScannerSupplier. The overrides may do any of the following:
        • Enable a check that is currently off
        • Disable a check that is currently on
        • Change the severity of a check that is on, promoting a warning to an error or demoting an error to a warning
        Parameters:
        errorProneOptions - an ErrorProneOptions object that encapsulates the overrides for this compilation
        Throws:
        InvalidCommandLineOptionException - if the override map attempts to disable a check that may not be disabled

      • plus

        @CheckReturnValue
public ScannerSupplier plus(ScannerSupplier other)
        Composes this ScannerSupplier with the other ScannerSupplier. The set of checks that are turned on is the union of the set of checks on in this and other.

      • filter

        @CheckReturnValue
public ScannerSupplier filter(com.google.common.base.Predicate<? super BugChecker> predicate)
        Filters this ScannerSupplier based on the provided predicate. Returns a ScannerSupplier with only the checks enabled that satisfy the predicate.
